<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1803,2015]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,153,935]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1839,1866]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Swinhoe, 1912" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[650,914,1839,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[650,729,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Spialia</emphasis>
Swinhoe, 1912
</taxonomicName>
, where these species were placed previously. Keys to 5, 15, 21 (exclude antithesis of 25), or thesis 
<quantity box="[759,816,1875,1902]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="de Jong, R." box="[824,1028,1875,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" pagination="23 - 146" refId="ref8814" refString="de Jong, R. (1978) Monograph of the genus Spialia Swinhoe (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 121, 23 - 146." type="journal article" year="1978">de Jong (1978: 28</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 30), constituting his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1875" box="[1298,1377,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colotes">
<emphasis box="[1298,1377,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">colotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">delagoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Plotz" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[286,369,1912,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromus">
<emphasis box="[286,369,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">dromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups. Differs from its relatives by the following characters. Ventral hindwing with straight median white band not separated into sports, i.e., white spot in cell RS-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1063,1071,1965,1979]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">1</subScript>
(space 6) joins central spot (discal cell) to the outer (and not inner) spot in cell Sc+ 
<collectionCode box="[726,746,1984,2010]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[746,754,2001,2015]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">1</subScript>
-RS (space 7), but in many species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[1178,1257,1984,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1178,1257,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Spialia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this band either broken into spots or directed basad at costa. While 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[735,814,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,814,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Spialia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species lack costal fold in males, some 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2020" box="[1272,1347,154,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1272,1347,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Ernsta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have costal fold (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1875" box="[346,425,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colotes">
<emphasis box="[346,425,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">colotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group). Species with costal fold are in addition characterized by the central white discal cell spot on dorsal forewing not closer to discocellular spot than to the basal cell spot and no two white spots are present above over the central cell spot (to distinguish from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Trimen" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[862,967,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Agyllia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asterodia">
<emphasis box="[862,967,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">asterodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group of 
<bibRefCitation author="de Jong, R." box="[1162,1330,261,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" pagination="23 - 146" refId="ref8814" refString="de Jong, R. (1978) Monograph of the genus Spialia Swinhoe (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 121, 23 - 146." type="journal article" year="1978">de Jong (1978)</bibRefCitation>
that does not belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2020" box="[311,386,298,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[311,386,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Ernsta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and hindwing submarginal pale spots in cells M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[951,959,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">1</subScript>
-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[993,1001,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
&amp; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1065,1073,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1108,1116,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">3</subScript>
(spaces 4 &amp; 5) offset basad from the rest of the submarginal spots. Species without costal fold either lack the basal white spots in discal cell on dorsal forewing, however, some white scales along cubital vein may be present forming a narrow streak (the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" box="[151,254,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
<emphasis box="[151,254,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">delagoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group), or on dorsal forewing in CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[766,774,422,436]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
-1 
<collectionCode box="[791,813,405,431]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
+2 
<collectionCode box="[844,866,405,431]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
cell (space 1 
<collectionCode box="[1008,1030,405,431]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
) the outer lower median spot absent and inner lower median spot not smaller than the outer upper median spot (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Plotz" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[980,1063,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromus">
<emphasis box="[980,1063,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">dromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group). In male genitalia, uncus not deeply incised, gnathos dorsally joined to tegumen, if gnathos free (in some species from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" box="[1334,1437,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
<emphasis box="[1334,1437,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">delagoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), then coecum of aedeagus shortened or absent. In DNA 
<collectionCode box="[855,903,513,539]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">COI</collectionCode>
barcode region, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: 
<collectionCode box="[422,443,549,575]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
