<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,153,935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,482,620,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Derivation of the name.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular. It honors Ernst Brockmann of Lich, 
<collectingCountry box="[250,354,657,683]" name="Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Germany</collectingCountry>
and his unstoppable passion for 
<taxonomicName box="[731,865,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
in general and the Grizzled skippers in particular. Without his enthusiasm, help, encouragement and specimens this study would not be accomplished.
</paragraph>
